    "reviews": [
      {
        "author_name": "jenn morrow",
        "rating": 4,
        "text": "Love this place!\nThe food and service was excellent!\nI do wish they had more open hours, but then they are open they are a gem!\nThey are a sustainable restaurant and use produce from their own garden. The food doesn’t get fresher than that!\nThey have inside and outside dining.\nThey also have great coffee/espresso!",
        "time": 1661298959,
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWszn7Gox8SQO-Iyhw1tBKYj77-pjIAEhk2txpbjsiHKcZMbbkq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"
      },
      {
        "author_name": "Becca Schilling",
        "rating": 5,
        "text": "We love Common Roots Cafe, and had them cater for our wedding. The food was absolutely *delicious*. Everyone loved it, and I still think about that turkey at least once a week. They went above and beyond with the planning process leading up to the wedding, and were so incredibly helpful and thoughtful. I loved getting to work with them, and cannot stress how much I appreciated all they did for us!\n\nI have dietary restrictions, and we selected passed apps for cocktail hour that I couldn't eat. They asked me ahead of time if I would like them to make a couple things special for me and I told them not worry about it as I'd have plenty of food shortly after for dinner time. They flagged me down during cocktail hour with a plate of specially made appetizers just for me. And I don't mean, like, a simple veggie tray or something. They specifically went out of their way to make a few gluten free and dairy free versions of the tarts we were serving guests, just for me. Unbelievable service and care.\n\nAmazing food, and incredible employees. We highly recommend both their catering and their cafe!",
        "time": 1640195394,
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQV-biSxPlvy4ennMyqZYDflM6SPhIUM98dO3R2Ye471DjxxUr=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo"
      },
      {
        "author_name": "Negma Farah",
        "rating": 5,
        "text": "We went here for weekend brunch. The food was great! My only complaint is that it’s outdoor seating and there could have been a couple of umbrellas. We did get a nice tan. :) the lavender latte is my fav!",
        "time": 1621899998,
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhhvedck8HMCyLt9k9XwzbyNN2XgNYMO1QPkiuETUnreQiX2GH_w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"
      },
      {
        "author_name": "Lynx Cheam",
        "rating": 5,
        "text": "Good times were had. Service was great. As part of my first time out to MN, I would say this place is easily worth the visit.\n\nWhen done with meal, you bus yourself. Keep that in mind, they don't spoil you here with service of that level, but instead exchange it for delicious food and tasty coffee.\n\nPictured: Shakshuka, Small Hot Mocha, Large Hot Salted Caramel",
        "time": 1665938155,
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4Va-wrVXvi0nyUzC3MgObVJTPd4_dIZscos4Bpp-WBPovpEKN=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"
      },
      {
        "author_name": "Micalie Kempfert",
        "rating": 5,
        "text": "Great local coffee shop with delicious food options! They have unique latte flavors - I tried the salted caramel which was delicious! Pictured is the broccoli and tomato frittata and the farmers breakfast- both of which were excellent! They also have delicious gluten free bread. There’s a good amount of seating and a nice outdoor patio!",
        "time": 1565461298,
        "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOvpkckHyQAj-uC5k2cLe2veH8dQxd1DeP7IcWErKDvd2O1xR9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"
      }
    ]
  },
